title: Print, "New York Charities - St. Barnabas House, 304 Mulberry Street", April 18, 1874
medium: Wood engraving printed in black ink on paper
provenance: Gift of Mrs. Cora E. Wilson
description: Horizontal rectangle containting four vignettes: Upper left shows two young women, with one knocking at door marked: "St. Barnabas"; upper center shows a woman wearing a cap and apron, and holding a key, framed by a doorway; upper right shows three women; and the lower shows a room with young women seated in groups, some about a center table.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "New York Charities - St. Barnabas House, 304 Mulberry Street", April 18, 1874.
April 18, 1874. Wood engraving printed in black ink on paper. Gift of Cora Wilson. 1939-70-7.
